"{\"abstract\":\"This paper presents computational approaches for automatically detecting critical plot twists in reviews of media products. First, we created a large-scale book review dataset that includes fine-grained spoiler annotations at the sentence-level, as well as book and (anonymized) user information. Second, we carefully analyzed this dataset, and found that: spoiler language tends to be book-specific; spoiler distributions vary greatly across books and review authors; and spoiler sentences tend to jointly appear in the latter part of reviews. Third, inspired by these findings, we developed an end-to-end neural network architecture to detect spoiler sentences in review corpora. Quantitative and qualitative results demonstrate that the proposed method substantially outperforms existing baselines.\",\"arxivId\":\"1905.13416\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2127553\",\"name\":\"Mengting Wan\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2127553\"},{\"authorId\":\"20187203\",\"name\":\"Rishabh Misra\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/20187203\"},{\"authorId\":\"134523604\",\"name\":\"Ndapa Nakashole\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/134523604\"},{\"authorId\":\"35660011\",\"name\":\"Julian McAuley\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/35660011\"}],\"citationVelocity\":6,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2007.05651\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"46275709\",\"name\":\"Jinfeng Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"47001493\",\"name\":\"Yuliang Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"47120191\",\"name\":\"Xiaolan Wang\"},{\"authorId\":\"115609743\",\"name\":\"W. Tan\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"result\",\"background\",\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":true,\"paperId\":\"dd5cc87ad4611dba35a25ef8866a21bf35dc179a\",\"title\":\"Deep or Simple Models for Semantic Tagging? It Depends on your Data\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/dd5cc87ad4611dba35a25ef8866a21bf35dc179a\",\"venue\":\"Proc. VLDB Endow.\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxivId\":null,\"a